---
// The broker–worker mesh, drawn as a wiring diagram.
// Pure HTML/CSS: boxes, hairline wires, mono annotations.
---

<figure class="mesh">
  <div class="mesh-node mesh-slack">
    <span class="node-kind">slack workspace</span>
    <span class="node-name">#your-channel · DMs · /pinet</span>
  </div>

  <div class="wire wire-down">
    <span class="wire-label">socket mode</span>
  </div>

  <div class="mesh-node mesh-broker">
    <span class="node-kind">broker</span>
    <span class="node-name">routing · thread ownership · RALPH loop</span>
  </div>

  <div class="wire wire-fan" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="wire-label">message.send</span>
  </div>

  <div class="mesh-workers">
    <div class="mesh-node mesh-worker">
      <span class="node-kind">worker</span>
      <span class="node-name">Rocket Dolphin</span>
      <span class="node-task">reviewing PR #123</span>
    </div>
    <div class="mesh-node mesh-worker">
      <span class="node-kind">worker</span>
      <span class="node-name">Silent Crocodile</span>
      <span class="node-task">fixing broken branch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="mesh-node mesh-worker">
      <span class="node-kind">worker</span>
      <span class="node-name">Pixel Lime Jaguar</span>
      <span class="node-task">running the tests</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <figcaption>
    fig. 1 — one broker owns routing and lifecycle; workers pick up threads, ship, and report back.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .mesh {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--mono);
  }

  .mesh-node {
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.1rem;
  }

  .node-kind {
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--signal);
  }

  .node-name {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .node-task {
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .mesh-broker {
    border-width: 2.5px;
  }

  .wire {
    position: relative;
    height: 2rem;
    margin-left: 1.6rem;
    border-left: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
  }

  /* A message pip travels the wire: workspace → broker → workers.
     The one purposeful animation on the page; it draws the actual data path. */
  .wire::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: -4.25px;
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    background: var(--signal);
    opacity: 0;
    animation: pip 4.8s linear infinite;
  }

  .wire-fan::after {
    animation-delay: 2.4s;
  }

  @keyframes pip {
    0% {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
    6% {
      opacity: 1;
    }
    40% {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(1.55rem);
    }
    48%,
    100% {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(1.55rem);
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .wire::after {
      animation: none;
      opacity: 0;
    }
  }

  .wire-label {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0.6rem;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .wire-fan {
    border-left: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .mesh-workers {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.6rem;
    border-top: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: 0.6rem;
  }

  .mesh-workers .mesh-node {
    border-style: solid;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-faint);
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .mesh-workers {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
